I think they probably mean impersonate in the sense of pretending to be some other existing person, such as a Mythic representative or another player.  In fact, the first sentence of the rule reads in its entirety, "[Player may not...] Impersonate any person, including, but not limited to, Mythic' employees, CSRs or hosts."<br>
<br>
The "roleplaying is not an excuse" rule, of course, just anticipates a lame but commonly-used excuse for antisocial behavior ("But I'm roleplaying a sexual deviant who likes to swear a lot!"). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umappill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mappill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/27/01 9:13:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alt-tab (background) functionality restored</span><hr size=1> I read only the first few responses, so this may be a duplicate thought.  I would like to have the ability to alt-tab for the sole purpose of being able to go find a map (maybe even print) or other useful info that might help me from having to log out and back in which takes some time.  As long as we are still vulernable, what difference does it make if we are not actively playing it.  It should act just like being AFK, just with the ability to do something else on the comp.  <br>
<br>
Heck, you could even have it up at work and alt-tab out when needed.   <br>
